modules.description: Creates and manipulates messages with a unique identifier, topic, quality of service, retain flag, and payload. Operates on a structured type that encapsulates these attributes. Used to construct and extract components of MQTT messages in communication protocols.

Provides access to version numbers through distinct integer values for major, minor, and revision components. Extracts individual parts of a version identifier for precise comparison and logging. Used to enforce version constraints in system checks and dependency management.

Handles MQTT protocol interactions by providing publish, subscribe, and connection management functions. Operates with string-based topics, message payloads, and client identifiers. Used to implement real-time message routing in IoT applications and event-driven systems.

Encapsulates MQTT message handling and version tracking through distinct types. Manages message attributes like ID, topic, QoS, retain flag, and payload, while extracting version components such as major, minor, and revision. Supports message construction, extraction, and version comparison for protocol compliance and system validation. Enables precise control over message formatting and version-based decision making in communication systems.
